sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Backend as Dashboard Backend<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Controller

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: User Authentication and Dashboard Access

    User->>Router: GET / (Initial request)
    Router->>Proxy: HTTPS/8443 (TLS reencrypt)
    Proxy->>OAuth: OAuth redirect (no token)
    OAuth->>User: Login page
    User->>OAuth: User credentials
    OAuth->>User: OAuth token (redirect)
    User->>Proxy: GET / with Bearer Token
    Proxy->>K8s: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>Proxy: Token valid, user authorized
    Proxy->>Backend: HTTP/8080<br/>X-Auth-Request-User header
    Backend-->>Proxy: Dashboard HTML + JS
    Proxy-->>User: HTTPS/8443 Dashboard UI

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: Notebook Creation

    User->>Proxy: POST /api/notebooks<br/>Bearer Token + Notebook spec
    Proxy->>K8s: Validate token
    K8s-->>Proxy: Valid
    Proxy->>Backend: HTTP/8080<br/>Impersonation headers
    Backend->>K8s: POST /apis/kubeflow.org/v1/notebooks<br/>ServiceAccount + Impersonation
    K8s->>Notebook: Create Notebook CR
    Notebook->>K8s: Create Pod, Service
    K8s-->>Backend: Notebook created (200 OK)
    Backend-->>Proxy: Success response
    Proxy-->>User: HTTPS/8443 Success (JSON)

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 3: WebSocket Resource Watch

    User->>Proxy: WebSocket Upgrade /wss/k8s/notebooks<br/>Bearer Token
    Proxy->>K8s: Validate token
    K8s-->>Proxy: Valid
    Proxy->>Backend: ws://localhost:8080/wss/k8s/notebooks<br/>Impersonation headers
    Backend->>K8s: Watch /apis/kubeflow.org/v1/notebooks<br/>wss://kubernetes.default.svc:443
    K8s-->>Backend: Stream notebook events
    Backend-->>Proxy: Stream events (ws://)
    Proxy-->>User: Stream events (wss://)

    Note over User,K8s: Flow 4: Prometheus Metrics Query

    User->>Proxy: POST /api/prometheus<br/>Bearer Token + PromQL
    Proxy->>Backend: HTTP/8080<br/>Impersonation headers
    Backend->>Prometheus: POST /api/v1/query<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Prometheus-->>Backend: Metrics data (JSON)
    Backend-->>Proxy: Metrics response
    Proxy-->>User: HTTPS/8443 Metrics (JSON)
